flowRoot.flowPara: Client and server negotiate protocol Version
Server sends its certificate which is checked agains public CA
Client sends its certificate which is checked against own root CA
Client sends pre-master key signed with servers public key
Client sends previos messages signed with its private key
If the msgs can be decrypted with the clients public key it is trusted to be the owner of the certificate.
Client and Server send finished msg decrypted using the master key
if both msg could be decrypted properly the handshake is completed. An authenticated encrypted connection has been etablished
